---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '@/config';
import Breadcrumbs from '@/components/Breadcrumbs.svelte';
import { getBreadcrumbSchema } from '@/lib/schemas';

const schema = getBreadcrumbSchema([
  { name: 'Privacy Policy', url: new URL('/privacy-policy', Astro.site).toString() },
]);

const lastUpdated = 'July 18, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`Privacy policy for ${SITE.website.replace('https://', '')} — what data is collected, how Google Analytics and ads are used, and how to reach ${SITE.author}.`}
  schema={schema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Privacy Policy', href: '/privacy-policy' }]} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-foreground leading-[1.1] mb-2">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-10">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <article class="prose max-w-none text-muted-foreground">
      <p>
        This site, themissingsunday.com, is run by me, Alwyn Y. — you can find out more about who I am
        on the <a href="/about">About page</a>. This policy explains what data gets collected when you
        visit, why, and what your options are. I've tried to write it in plain English rather than
        legal boilerplate.
      </p>

      <h2>What gets collected</h2>
      <p>Like most websites, this one collects a few kinds of data automatically:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Server logs</strong> — standard web server logs (IP address, browser type, pages
          requested, timestamps) generated as part of serving the site. This is infrastructure-level
          logging, not something I actively review per-visitor.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cookies</strong> — small files stored in your browser, used for things like
          remembering your dark/light theme preference and for analytics (below).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Google Analytics</strong> — I use Google Analytics to understand traffic patterns
          (which posts get read, roughly where visitors come from, that kind of thing). It sets its own
          cookies and collects the usual analytics data points (pages visited, session duration, device/
          browser type, approximate location). I don't use this to identify individual visitors.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Advertising (Google AdSense)</h2>
      <p>
        This site uses, or intends to use, <strong>Google AdSense</strong> to serve ads. Google, as a
        third-party vendor, uses cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this site and
        others. Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on
        your visit to this site and/or other sites on the Internet. You can read more about how Google
        uses this data on Google's own page,{' '}
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          "How Google uses information from sites or apps that use our services."
        </a>
      </p>
      <p>
        Third-party vendors, including Google, may also use cookies to serve ads based on your past
        visits to this site for ad personalization. You can opt out of personalized advertising by
        visiting{' '}
        <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Google's Ads Settings
        </a>{' '}
        or, for a broader opt-out across participating ad networks, the{' '}
        <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Digital Advertising Alliance's opt-out page
        </a>.
      </p>

      <h2>TransitPulse (a related project)</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://transitpulse.themissingsunday.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          TransitPulse
        </a> is a separate side project of mine hosted on a subdomain of this site. It does not use any
        analytics or send data to a server — it only uses your browser's Geolocation API (with your
        permission, to center the map on your location) and browser <code>localStorage</code> (to
        remember things like your saved home location and display preferences locally on your own
        device). None of that data leaves your browser or reaches me.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        If you're in a region covered by GDPR, CCPA, or similar privacy laws, you have the right to
        ask what data (if any) is held about you, request it be deleted, or just ask questions about
        any of the above. Since this is a personal site rather than a service you sign up for, there's
        no account data to speak of — but if you have concerns, reach out via{' '}
        <a href={SITE.social.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a> and I'll
        get back to you.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If anything material changes — a new analytics tool, a new ad network, a new subdomain project
        that collects data — I'll update this page and the "last updated" date above.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
